Danida exhibits a strong preference for earmarked funding—about 23% median share—indicating a strategic, targeted allocation approach. Funding is regionally diverse, with priority areas including East Africa, Asia, Europe, and global initiatives, reflecting shifting geographic focus and increasing outreach from 8 to 24 recipient countries (2022-2024). This visualization presents the funding volatility of Denmark’s Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Danida, measured by transaction value over time. The data spans 71 funding transactions from February 2023 to December 2025. Denmark’s average transaction amount is 1.5 million US dollars with an average of 23.7 transactions per year. Compared to the benchmark of the top 10 other donors, which have an average transaction amount of 2.9 million dollars and 371.3 transactions per year, Danida’s funding activity is both smaller in size and substantially less frequent. Transaction values show variability without clear upward or downward trends, highlighting a relatively stable but low-frequency funding pattern.
